cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is about a natural language processing task (hierarchical classification of German blurbs) and uses machine learning techniques (TF-IDF extraction and linear SVM classifier). Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This sub-category covers topics related to natural language processing and computational linguistics. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): This sub-category covers topics related to search engines, information retrieval, and text mining. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category covers topics related to machine learning algorithms and applications. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category covers topics related to artificial intelligence, including natural language processing and machine learning. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): This sub-category covers topics related to algorithms and data structures, which are relevant for the machine learning techniques used in this paper.
